items.title: 28 Days Later
items.description: Twenty-eight days after the outbreak of a deadly virus in London, which infects everyone and turns them into braindead killers, the survivors try to cope with their losses and find sanctuary.endurance.

items.title: Rampant
items.description: When his older brother dies, Lee Chung returns to Joseon to protect his sibling's spouse and unborn child, only to confront a powerful government official who unleashes a horde of zombies.

items.title: The Elephant Whisperers
items.description: Bomman and Bellie, a couple in South India, devote their lives to caring for an orphaned baby elephant named Raghu, forging a family like no other that tests the barrier between the human and the animal world.

items.title: 28 Weeks Later
items.description: When an incurable virus starts killing people in Britain, they are forced to evacuate their homes. All hell breaks loose when they try to return to their country and are again attacked by the virus.

items.title: 28 Years Later
items.description: It's been almost three decades since the rage virus escaped from a biological weapons laboratory. Still living in a ruthlessly enforced quarantine, some have found ways to exist amid the infected. One such group of survivors lives on a small island connected to the mainland by a single, heavily defended causeway. When one of them decides to venture into the dark heart of the mainland, he soon discovers a mutation that has spread to not only the infected, but other survivors as well.

items.title: Furiosa: A Mad Max Saga
items.description: Snatched from the Green Place of Many Mothers, young Furiosa gets caught in the crossfire of two tyrannical warlords. As the tyrants fight for dominance, Furiosa soon finds herself in a nonstop battle to make her way home.

items.title: Spotlight
items.description: A team of journalists from The Boston Globe exposes systemic sexual abuse by clergy within the Catholic Church. Their investigation uncovers decades of cover-ups, shaking institutions and sparking global change.

items.title: Emancipation
items.description: Inspired by true events, this film follows Peter, a slave who escapes from a brutal Louisiana plantation. Enduring harrowing conditions in the swamps, he clings to hope and love for his family while challenging the injustices of his time. A testament to resilience and the human spirit.

items.title: The Kitchen
items.description: In a near-future London, young Izi tries to escape The Kitchen, a harsh zone left behind by the rich. His journey explores inequality, family, and hope.

items.title: The Wonder
items.description: In 19th-century Ireland, a nurse investigates a girl who has supposedly survived without food for months. She uncovers dark secrets threatening the entire community.

items.title: Leave the World Behind
items.description: A familys holiday is disrupted by strangers warning of an unfolding cyberattack. As systems fail, fear and mistrust consume everyone inside the house.

items.title: Spaceman
items.description: Alone on a cosmic mission, astronaut Jakub encounters a mysterious creature. As they connect, he reflects on lost relationships and his place in the universe.

items.title: May December
items.description: An actress preparing to play a controversial woman visits her and uncovers layers of deception, complicating the boundary between fiction and truth.

items.title: Oblivion
items.description: In a post-apocalyptic future, drone technician Jack Harper uncovers secrets about Earths destruction and his own existence. As he questions everything he knows, he becomes humanitys last hope in a fight against alien invaders and technological oppression.

items.title: Free Guy
items.description: Guy, a bank teller, realizes hes a non-player character in a video game. With the help of a programmer, he fights to save his virtual world from destruction, delivering laughs, action, and heartfelt moments along the way.

items.title: Encanto
items.description: The Madrigal family lives in a magical house in the mountains of Colombia, with each member blessed with a unique gift  except Mirabel. When the magic begins to fade, Mirabel takes it upon herself to save their extraordinary home and family.

items.title: Sir Alex
items.description: "Sir Alex" delves into the life and career of Sir Alex Ferguson, the most successful football manager in Manchester Uniteds history. The film explores his leadership, tactics, and the legacy he left behind in the footballing world.

items.title: The Pale Blue Eye
items.description: Set in 1830, a historical thriller where a detective, with the help of Edgar Allan Poe, investigates murders at a military academy.

items.title: Fly Me to the Moon
items.description: This delightful animated film follows three young flies as they stow away aboard the Apollo 11 mission. Filled with humor, adventure, and heartwarming moments, the movie showcases their out-of-this-world escapades and friendships.

items.title: Still Up
items.description: The movie follows the story of two people who connect online late at night and develop a deep bond. As they open up about their lives, they explore their own mental health struggles and learn to heal together.

items.title: If
items.description: After a traumatic event, a young girl named Bea gains the unique gift to see everyones forgotten imaginary friends. She embarks on a heartfelt journey to reunite these friends with their grown-up companions, leading to whimsical adventures and heartfelt lessons about imagination, love, and loss.

items.title: A Charlie Brown Christmas
items.description: Charlie Brown seeks the true meaning of Christmas amid holiday commercialism. With its simple message, iconic music, and lovable characters, this classic continues to charm audiences young and old.

items.title: Knives Out
items.description: When renowned mystery novelist Harlan Thrombey is found dead, Detective Benoit Blanc must untangle a web of family secrets, lies, and motives. This comedic take on a classic murder mystery is filled with twists and quirky characters.

items.title: The Six Triple Eight
items.description: The true story of the 6888th Postal Battalion, a group of African-American women who tackled a mail backlog during WWII, highlighting their dedication and overlooked contributions.

items.title: 9/11: Inside the President's War Room
items.description: Through never-before-seen footage and interviews with key figures, this documentary explores the critical decisions made by President Bush and his administration in the hours following the September 11 attacks.

items.title: Spider-Man 3
items.description: When Peter Parker bonds with an alien symbiote, his personality changes, making him aggressive. Meanwhile, he faces new villains, Sandman and Venom, while struggling to keep his relationships intact.

items.title: Spider-Man 2
items.description: As Peter Parker faces personal struggles, his abilities begin to fade. Meanwhile, Dr. Otto Octavius becomes Doctor Octopus, a deadly foe who threatens the city. Peter must embrace his responsibility to save those he loves.

items.title: Argylle
items.description: Bestselling spy novelist Argylle becomes entangled in a real-life international espionage conspiracy. Packed with comedic misunderstandings, high-octane action, and a star-studded cast, the movie reinvents the spy genre with humor and charm.

items.title: The Revenant
items.description: Hugh Glass, a frontiersman left for dead after a bear attack, embarks on an epic journey of survival. Battling nature and betrayal, his determination to seek vengeance drives him to the limits of human endurance.

items.title: Spider-Man
items.description: Peter Parker, an ordinary high school student, gains spider-like abilities and struggles to balance his newfound powers with his personal life. As he learns the responsibility of being Spider-Man, he must also battle the villainous Green Goblin.

items.title: Challengers
items.description: Challengers follows Tashi Duncan, a former tennis prodigy turned coach, who has transformed her husband, Art Donaldson, into a champion. To overcome a recent losing streak and redeem himself, Art faces his former rival, Patrick, in a high-stakes match on the ATP Challenger Tour. The film delves into themes of ambition, rivalry, and the complexities of relationships within the competitive sports arena.

items.title: Dune: Part One
items.description: Dune is the story of Paul Atreides, who must secure his family's future while navigating politics, war, and prophecy on the dangerous desert planet of Arrakis.

items.title: The Social Dilemma
items.description: This eye-opening documentary reveals the dark side of social media, showcasing how algorithms manipulate human behavior. Interviews with tech insiders and experts highlight the ethical dilemmas and societal impacts of these platforms.

items.title: The Irishman
items.description: Frank Sheeran recounts his decades-long involvement with organized crime, exploring his connections with infamous mobsters and reflecting on the personal cost of his choices in this epic story of loyalty and betrayal.

items.title: Spider-Man: No Way Home
items.description: After his secret identity is exposed, Peter Parker seeks help from Doctor Strange. A spell goes wrong, bringing villains from other universes, forcing Peter to make difficult choices.

items.title: Jojo Rabbit
items.description: In Nazi Germany, a young boy named Jojo discovers his mother is hiding a Jewish girl in their home. Guided by his imaginary friend, Adolf Hitler, he begins questioning his beliefs, leading to moments of humor, heartbreak, and self-discovery.

items.title: The Nice Guys
items.description: Private eye Holland March and enforcer Jackson Healy team up to investigate the disappearance of a young woman. Set in the 1970s, their misadventures combine slapstick humor with a gripping mystery.

items.title: Palm Springs
items.description: Nyles and Sarah meet at a wedding, only to find themselves stuck in a time loop, reliving the same day over and over. As they navigate their bizarre predicament, romance and hilarity ensue in this refreshing and witty comedy.

items.title: CODA
items.description: Ruby, the only hearing member of her family, balances her love for singing and her familys reliance on her as their interpreter. This heartfelt story mixes humor and emotion, celebrating individuality and the beauty of familial bonds.

items.title: Palmer
items.description: After serving time in prison, Eddie Palmer returns to his small-town roots, hoping to rebuild his life. He forms an unlikely friendship with a young boy named Sam, who faces bullying for being different. The heartfelt narrative explores redemption, acceptance, and the transformative power of love.

items.title: Flee
items.description: This groundbreaking film tells the story of Amin, an Afghan refugee, through innovative animation. It recounts his harrowing escape from his homeland and the emotional toll of displacement while balancing identity, family, and love.

items.title: Society of the Snow
items.description: Following the 1972 Andes plane crash, survivors endure brutal conditions and face impossible decisions. This gripping story is based on true events that reveal the limits of human survival.

items.title: Icarus
items.description: "Icarus" follows filmmaker Bryan Fogel as he unintentionally uncovers one of the biggest doping scandals in sports history, exposing Russias state-sponsored doping program and its far-reaching consequences.

items.title: Rustin
items.description: Bayard Rustin, a brilliant strategist of the civil rights movement, overcomes prejudice and politics to organize the historic 1963 March on Washington, changing the course of American history.

items.title: Spider-Man: Far From Home
items.description: Following the death of Tony Stark, Peter struggles with his role as a hero. While on a school trip, he is recruited by Nick Fury to fight elemental monsters and faces a deceptive new ally, Mysterio.

items.title: Every Goal
items.description: "Every Goal" showcases the most breathtaking goals scored in football, from stunning free-kicks to acrobatic volleys, capturing the beauty of the sport in its purest form.

items.title: Arrival
items.description: When alien ships appear around the globe, linguist Louise Banks is recruited to decipher their language. As she unravels their complex communication, she discovers truths that transcend time and challenge perception.

items.title: Deep Sea
items.description: A young girl's journey into the depths of the ocean leads her to discover a vibrant yet perilous realm, where she embarks on an adventure of self-discovery and courage.

items.title: O.J.: Made in America
items.description: "O.J.: Made in America" is a gripping five-part documentary exploring the rise and fall of O.J. Simpson, from his football stardom to his infamous murder trial, highlighting themes of race, celebrity, and justice in America.

items.title: The Amazing Spider-Man 2
items.description: Peter Parker continues his double life as Spider-Man but faces a new powerful enemy, Electro. Meanwhile, he discovers shocking secrets about his past and his connection to Oscorp.

items.title: The Killer
items.description: A professional assassin begins to question his work and identity after a job goes wrong. Battling his employers and inner demons, he embarks on a violent path of self-discovery.

items.title: His Three Daughters
items.description: Three estranged sisters come together to care for their dying father. In the process, they confront past wounds, misunderstandings, and the bonds that hold them together.

items.title: Shirley
items.description: Shirley Chisholms rise to Congress and her run for president showcase her resilience and courage. Her campaign inspires generations and challenges the political status quo.

items.title: Wolfwalkers
items.description: This visually stunning film follows Robyn, a young hunter, who befriends Mebh, a wolfwalker. Together, they navigate magical forests, challenging family loyalties and societal expectations, creating a touching story of courage and friendship.- 2

items.title: Blood & Gold
items.description: In the closing days of WWII, a German deserter and a young woman team up against brutal SS troops in search of hidden gold. Together, they fight for survival and justice in a war-torn village.

items.title: Sharper
items.description: Set in the glitzy world of Manhattans elite, Sharper follows a series of interconnected cons as characters manipulate one another in a high-stakes game of betrayal and ambition. With every twist and reveal, the line between predator and prey blurs in this stylish and gripping drama.

items.title: SENA
items.description: "SENA" follows the career and tragic demise of Ayrton Senna, one of the greatest F1 drivers of all time. Through rare footage and interviews, the film gives an emotional insight into his journey and impact on the sport.

items.title: Lift
items.description: A skilled thief and his crew plan an ambitious heist aboard a high-security flight. With FBI watching and time running out, the mission quickly spirals into chaos.

items.title: Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse
items.description: A young Brooklyn teen, Miles Morales, becomes Spider-Man and meets alternate versions of himself from different dimensions. Together, they must stop the Kingpin from destroying reality.

items.title: Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse
items.description: Miles Morales is reunited with Gwen Stacy and is drawn into a vast Spider-Society, where he encounters new threats and conflicts that challenge his heroism.

items.title: A Charlie Brown Thanksgiving
items.description: Charlie Brown hosts a Thanksgiving dinner for his friends, with humorous mishaps and heartfelt moments. This timeless animated special celebrates friendship and the holiday spirit with its lovable characters.

items.title: Maestro
items.description: Told through a nonlinear narrative, the film explores the artistic achievements and emotional struggles of composer Leonard Bernstein, focusing on his marriage and creative genius.

items.title: Napoleon
items.description: A historical epic that delves into the life of Napoleon Bonaparte, chronicling his meteoric rise from an ambitious soldier to Emperor of France. The film captures his military genius, political maneuvering, and personal struggles, highlighting key events that shaped European history.

items.title: Nyad
items.description: Diana Nyad attempts an incredible 110-mile swim from Cuba to Florida at age 64. Facing physical and emotional challenges, her story highlights human endurance and the power of never giving up.

items.title: 14 Peaks
items.description: "14 Peaks: Nothing Is Impossible" follows Nepalese mountaineer Nirmal Purja as he embarks on a record-breaking journey to climb the world's 14 tallest mountains in under seven months. The film captures the extreme challenges, triumphs, and the spirit of human endurance.

items.title: The Sky is Everywhere
items.description: After the death of her sister, Lennie must navigate the intense feelings of grief and love, torn between two boys while learning how to move forward and honor her sister's memory.

items.title: Inside Out 2
items.description: Inside Out 2 follows Riley as she navigates the difficult transition into adolescence. The story introduces new emotionsAnxiety, Embarrassment, Envy, and Ennuiwho take on important roles in Rileys internal world. As Riley adjusts to life in junior high, these new emotions help her confront her fears and self-doubt while offering insights into the importance of mental health, self-expression, and personal growth.

items.title: Ghosted
items.description: Cole falls head over heels for Sadie, only to discover shes a secret agent. Their relationship takes a wild turn as they team up on a globe-trotting mission to save the world, blending romance, action, and laugh-out-loud moments.

items.title: Spirited
items.description: This musical comedy stars Will Ferrell and Ryan Reynolds in a hilarious retelling of the classic story. Packed with catchy songs, witty dialogue, and heartfelt moments, its a perfect holiday film for the family.

items.title: The Amazing Spider-Man
items.description: Peter Parker discovers a hidden secret about his parents, leading him to Dr. Curt Connors, who transforms into the Lizard. Peter embraces his Spider-Man persona to protect New York.

items.title: The Redeem Team
items.description: "The Redeem Team" chronicles the journey of the 2008 U.S. mens basketball team, which aimed to reclaim Olympic glory after a disappointing finish in 2004. With stars like Kobe Bryant and LeBron James, the film showcases their determination to restore U.S. dominance in the sport.

items.title: The French Dispatch
items.description: A love letter to journalists, this comedy-drama anthology brings to life stories from a fictional magazine in 20th-century France. Featuring an ensemble cast, the film is a mix of quirky humor, stunning visuals, and heartfelt moments.

items.title: Fire of Love
items.description: Katia and Maurice Krafft, a pair of volcanologists, shared a passion for studying active volcanoes. Their extraordinary footage and story celebrate love, science, and their ultimate sacrifice in pursuit of understanding the Earth.

items.title: Still: A Michael J. Fox Movie
items.description: This heartfelt documentary follows the life of Michael J. Fox, detailing his rise to fame, his battle with Parkinson's disease, and his unyielding determination to live life to the fullest despite his challenges.

items.title: Luca
items.description: Two sea monsters, Luca and Alberto, explore the human world in a picturesque Italian town while keeping their true identities hidden. Filled with humor, charm, and heartfelt lessons, its a celebration of friendship and self-acceptance.

items.title: My Octopus Teacher
items.description: A filmmaker forges an unusual friendship with an octopus in a South African kelp forest. This visually stunning and emotionally touching documentary explores the interconnectedness of humans and nature.

items.title: Free Solo
items.description: This Academy Award-winning documentary captures Alex Honnolds daring attempt to climb El Capitan without ropes, delving into his psychological preparation, physical endurance, and the stunning landscapes he conquers.

items.title: 13th
items.description: This thought-provoking documentary examines the intersection of race, justice, and mass incarceration in the United States, shedding light on the systemic inequalities rooted in the 13th Amendment.

items.title: The Bloody Hundredth
items.description: This documentary chronicles the harrowing missions of the 100th Bomb Group during World War II. Known for their heavy losses, their bravery and sacrifice are brought to life through rare footage and veterans' accounts.

items.title: Scoop
items.description: The story behind the infamous Prince Andrew interview, revealing the persistence, tactics, and courage of the women journalists who secured the royal scandal.

items.description: A documentary series detailing Manchester United's historic 199899 season, during which the club won the Premier League, FA Cup, and UEFA Champions League, featuring interviews with players and staff involved in the triumph.

items.title: Damsel
items.description: Promised a royal marriage, Elodie is instead trapped in a cave with a fire-breathing dragon. She must fight to survive and reclaim her destiny.

items.title: Time Cut
items.description: Lucy uses a time portal to travel back to high school in 2003, aiming to stop her sisters murder. But navigating teen life and confronting a serial killer isn't easy.

items.title: Bread and Roses
items.description: This moving documentary follows the resilience of Afghan women facing oppression under the Taliban regime, highlighting their struggles for basic rights and freedoms while balancing family and personal aspirations.

items.title: Rebel Moon
items.description: Kora, a former soldier, assembles a band of fighters to resist the oppressive Motherworld and save a peaceful settlement. The film is a visually rich space opera of rebellion and hope.

items.title: Spider-Man: Homecoming
items.description: After the events of Civil War, Peter Parker struggles to prove himself as a hero while balancing school and social life. He encounters the dangerous Vulture, testing his abilities and responsibility.

items.title: The Secret Life of Pets
items.description: The Secret Life of Pets reveals the secret lives of pets when their owners are away. The film follows Max, a Jack Russell Terrier, who is forced to share his home with a new dog, Duke. When the two pets get lost in the city, they must work together to find their way back home, encountering several challenges, including a rebellious rabbit named Snowball. The film is filled with comedic moments and heartwarming themes about friendship and loyalty.

items.title: Gladiator 2
items.description: Following the legacy of Maximus Decimus Meridius, this sequel focuses on Lucius, the young boy who idolized him. Now grown, Lucius navigates the treacherous political landscape of Rome, facing challenges that test his courage, loyalty, and leadership.

items.title: Pele
items.description: An intimate portrait of Brazilian football legend Pel, covering his journey from a teenager winning the World Cup to a national hero, with rare interviews and archival footage.

items.title: The Figo Affair
items.description: A deep dive into Lus Figos controversial transfer from FC Barcelona to Real Madrid, exploring the political, cultural, and sporting tensions that defined this pivotal moment in football.

items.title: The Class of '92
items.description: A documentary charting the rise of six Manchester United academy graduatesDavid Beckham, Nicky Butt, Ryan Giggs, Gary Neville, Phil Neville, and Paul Scholesdetailing their journey from youth prospects to key figures in the club's treble-winning 1999 season.

items.title: United
items.description: A BBC television film depicting the tragic Munich air disaster that claimed the lives of eight Manchester United players, focusing on assistant manager Jimmy Murphy's efforts to rebuild the team and the emotional journey of the survivors.

items.title: Diego Maradona
items.description: A powerful documentary about the legendary Argentine footballer Diego Maradona, featuring rare archival footage and focusing on his tumultuous time at Napoli and struggles with fame, addiction, and pressure.

items.title: Take the Ball, Pass the Ball
items.description: Showcasing FC Barcelonas golden era under Pep Guardiola, the documentary highlights tactical brilliance, key players like Messi, Xavi, and Iniesta, and the teams dominance from 2008 to 2012.

items.title: Rooney
items.description: This documentary reflects on Wayne Rooneys incredible football career, his personal life, challenges faced with fame, and his evolution from a teenage sensation to a respected football icon.

items.title: All or Nothing: Arsenal
items.description: A documentary series that offers unprecedented access into Arsenal Football Clubs 2021/22 campaign, showcasing locker room moments, intense matches, player relationships, and the managers perspective.

items.title: Beckham
items.description: A comprehensive documentary on football icon David Beckham, featuring personal interviews, family insights, and a deep dive into his rise from working-class London to global superstardom.

items.title: Dune: Part Two
items.description: Paul Atreides unites desert warriors to fight back against the forces that destroyed his family. This visually stunning sequel delves deeper into his destiny, as alliances and betrayals shape the future of the galaxy.
